CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 9, 1954, pg. 16 reads: "Visitor - Pete Shelton, whose sister is the owner of Charleston, W. Va.'s Red Star Taxi Co., and who, himself, has been employed by the Ownes-Illinois Glass Company for the last eleven years, stopped at the Ellis Hotel while on vacation in Pittsburgh this week. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Pete Shelton wearing double breasted suit jacket and necktie with leaf, standing in interior with light colored walls, stack of books, and door with signs, possibly Pittsburgh Courier offices
